Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrots{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Core and cut the @apple{2} into 8 wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the carrots onto one side of another large baking tray.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Place the @British Cumberland sausages{8} onto the other side of the carrot tray. Roast on the middle shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

When turning the sausages halfway through, add the apple wedges to the carrot side of the tray. Drizzle @oil{} over them and toss to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. They're cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the wedges have 5 mins remaining, remove the tray from the oven, sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}, then pop back into the oven for the remaining time.

Once the carrots and apples are roasted, remove the tray from the oven and drizzle over the @apple and sage jelly{37%grams}.

Toss together so both are evenly glazed.

Transfer the sausages to your plates.

Serve with the cheesy wedges and sticky apples and carrots alongside.

Finish with a dollop of @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} alongside for dipping.

Enjoy!